news.title: Hong Kong allows cheaper home purchases for investment visas
news.para: Hong Kong is reducing the investment threshold for residential property purchases under its investor visa program to HK$30 million, aiming to stimulate its struggling property market. This adjustment, announced by Chief Executive John Lee, seeks to attract more investment amid oversupply and economic challenges.

news.title: Court ‘crossed limits’, says Bombay HC, gives back 16-acre plot to builder
news.para: Bombay High Court intervened in a land dispute near Dahisar. The court reinstated a magistrate's order favoring Romell Housing. This order declared Romell Housing in possession of the land in April 2017. The court directed the receiver to hand over the plot to Romell Housing.

news.title: Tamil Nadu Housing Board pitches commercial hubs cheaper than private rentals
news.para: Tamil Nadu Housing Board is offering commercial complexes across Chennai at budget-friendly rates, nearly 20% cheaper than private rentals, attracting government departments like EPFO and GST. Seven complexes in prime locations with metro connectivity are proving attractive. TNHB seeks private sector participation for upcoming projects in Peters Colony, Arumbakkam, and Ashok Nagar, with 70% of available space already rented.

news.title: Delhi HC asks Ambuja Cements & JSW Cement to mediate 'kawach' trademark dispute amicably
news.para: The Delhi High Court has directed Ambuja Cements and JSW Cement to engage in mediation to resolve their trademark infringement dispute concerning the "kawach" trademark. Ambuja Cements alleges that JSW Cement's "Jal Kavach" cement infringes upon its registered "Ambuja Kawach" trademark, used since 2020 for water-repellent cement.

news.title: Ghaziabad property prices set to go up as Uttar Pradesh proposes 40% hike in circle rates
news.para: Ghaziabad is poised for a property price surge as the district administration plans to increase circle rates by up to 40%. Residential plots may see a 5-15% rise, while flats in large townships could jump by 35-40%. Commercial and industrial properties are also slated for significant hikes, impacting property transactions due to increased stamp duty and registration fees.

news.title: Kerala government assures smooth fund flow for Life Mission houses
news.para: Kerala's Life Mission project has provided 4,62,412 families with completed houses since 2017, with 1,33,124 more under construction, aiming to reach over six lakh beneficiaries by the government's term end. Minister Rajesh addressed assembly concerns about funding delays, highlighting the state's Rs 4 lakh contribution per house, significantly higher than the central PM Awas Yojana.

news.title: Developer, seven others booked for selling mortgaged flats in Dehu Road area
news.para: A developer in Dehu, along with seven others, has been booked for allegedly defrauding eight home buyers of ₹1.84 crore. They sold flats in a Malinagar housing complex that were already mortgaged to a credit society. The developer failed to disclose the loan to MahaRERA, violating regulations and leading to a police investigation for cheating and breach of trust.

news.title: SC directs states, UTs to strengthen real estate bodies
news.para: The Supreme Court has directed states and Union Territories to bolster their RERA authorities with adequate staffing, infrastructure, and legal expertise. These directives aim to prevent RERA bodies from becoming ineffective and ensure timely order implementation.

news.title: HC refuses relief to Ansal properties, says HRERA penalties must be faced despite insolvency
news.para: The Punjab and Haryana High Court has upheld interim penalty orders issued by HRERA against Ansal Properties for non-compliance with RERA Act, stating that insolvency proceedings do not exempt the company from statutory obligations.

news.title: Builder booked for cheating bank of ₹16.49 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Yash builders and its proprietor, Paras Dedhia, face accusations of cheating and criminal breach of trust after Axis Bank filed a complaint regarding a ₹16.49 crore loan for the Yash Signature project. Dedhia allegedly defaulted on repayments, failed to open an escrow account, and sold mortgaged properties without the bank's consent, leading to the account being declared NPA.

news.title: First property circle rate hike for Kolkata in seven years to push up registration fee, stamp duty
news.para: Kolkata property buyers face increased stamp duty and registration fees as the government raises circle rates by 15% to 90%, effective Wednesday. This revision, after seven years, aims to bridge the gap between circle and market rates. While officials justify the move, developers fear suppressed demand due to rates exceeding market prices in some areas.

news.title: Imposition of higher property tax rate on luxury hotels by MCD not arbitrary: Delhi HC
news.para: The Delhi High Court has upheld the Municipal Corporation of Delhi's higher property tax rates on luxury hotels, stating it's not arbitrary due to the affluent clientele they attract. The court dismissed petitions from hotels challenging the tax hike based on star ratings, deeming the classification rational and aligned with the economic capacity of their patrons.

news.title: Dubai Investments plans IPO of real estate unit Dubai Investments Park
news.para: Dubai Investments is considering an initial public offering for its Dubai Investments Park real estate business, aiming to sell up to a 25% stake. The IPO, potentially valuing DIP at $2.5 billion, is planned for the first quarter of next year, capitalizing on Dubai's real estate boom and increased infrastructure spending.

news.title: British real estate investor PRS REIT plans to sell unit for $881.2 million
news.para: PRS REIT is set to sell its property assets, held under PRS REIT Holding Company, to a Waypoint Asset Management-advised fund for approximately £646.2 million. This decision follows a strategic review initiated last October and a formal sale process.

news.title: Rithm Capital to acquire Paramount Group for $1.6 billion
news.para: Rithm Capital has agreed to acquire Paramount Group, a real estate investment trust, for $1.6 billion in cash, signaling a bet on the office real estate market's potential rebound. The offer represents a discount to Paramount's last closing price, as investors closely monitor the U.S. office market amid challenges from rising interest rates and remote work trends.

news.title: Indiabulls AMC, others settle AIF rules violations case with Sebi
news.para: Indiabulls Asset Management Company, now Groww AMC, along with its schemes and former officials, settled a case with Sebi for Rs 1.43 crore. The settlement resolves alleged violations of alternative investment fund rules dating back to 2017. Sebi had issued show cause notices alleging infractions like pledging scheme assets and misrepresenting financial information, which the entities addressed without admitting wrongdoing.

news.title: Former director of Lodha Developers arrested in fraud case
news.para: Rajendra Lodha, a former director of Lodha Developers Ltd, was arrested for allegedly defrauding the company of Rs 85 crore. He misused his position through fraudulent land deals and selling company land at deflated prices. The company stated Lodha resigned on August 17, 2025, after an ethics review and maintains a zero-tolerance policy towards misconduct.

news.title: Single-family housing starts in USA drop 7% in August
news.para: U.S. single-family homebuilding plummeted to a near 2-1/2-year low in August due to a glut of unsold new houses, signaling a potential economic headwind. Single-family housing starts fell 7.0%, and permits dropped to their lowest level in over two years. Builders are cutting prices to reduce inventory, while economists anticipate residential investment to drag on GDP growth until mid-2026.

news.title: Gurugram: Three towers demolished in Chintels Paradiso
news.para: A recent review meeting addressed the demolition progress at Chintels Paradiso in Gurugram, excluding the builder and RWA president. While four towers are nearly down, the demolition of Tower D is expected soon, paving the way for reconstruction.

news.title: SC restrains Supertech Realtors from creating third party rights in 'Supernova' project
news.para: The Supreme Court has restricted Supertech Realtors and its director from creating third-party rights in the Supernova project in Noida. The court also included the Noida Authority as a party in the matter. The suspended director must cooperate with the interim resolution professional. The court is considering a court-monitored resolution process. The next hearing is scheduled for October 8.
